%% 3.1.1 System Authentication (Login) — sequence diagram
%% Aligns with: Admin URL guard, Login UI, POST JWT, success toast + dashboard, fail alert.
%% Backend reference: POST api/Account/Login → AccountService.LoginAsync → JwtService.

sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User as User
    participant SPA as Admin SPA (Router Auth)
    participant Login as Login page (Card UI)
    participant API as Account API (POST Login)

    User->>SPA: Open Admin URL (e.g. admin.faceride.com)
    SPA->>SPA: Read Cookie / stored JWT
    alt No valid token
        SPA->>User: Redirect to /login
        SPA->>Login: Render Login page
        Login->>User: Show Logo, Email, Password, Login, EN/VI
    else Valid token
        SPA->>User: Enter app (e.g. Dashboard) — out of scope here
    end

    User->>Login: Enter email, password (masked)
    User->>Login: Click Login
    Login->>Login: Set button to loading spinner
    Login->>API: POST /api/Account/Login { email, password, deviceToken? }

    alt Login success
        API->>API: Validate user, BCrypt, issue JWT
        API-->>Login: 200 + JWT Bearer token
        Login->>Login: Stop spinner
        Login->>User: Toast MSG20 (green): Login successful
        Login->>SPA: Store token (cookie / storage)
        SPA->>User: Navigate to Dashboard + show sidebar
    else Wrong email or password
        API-->>Login: 400 + error message
        Login->>Login: Stop spinner
        Login->>User: Red alert above Email: login failed
        Note over Login: User can correct fields and retry (BR01: no Register here)
    end
